Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil. Chop the @new potatoes{1}(cut into 2cm cubes, no need to peel). Add the potatoes to your pan of boiling water and cook until tender, about ~{10%minutes}. Be careful not to overcook them!

Halve the @spring onions{3} lengthways, then thinly slice. Finely chop the @celery stick{1/2}. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(stalks and all). Trim the tops from the @green beans{1} and then cut them in half.

Lay a @British chicken breasts{2} on a #chopping board{}, place your hand flat on top and slice into it from the side so you can open it up like a book. This is called 'butterflying'! Repeat with the remaining chicken then don't forget to wash your hands, knife and chopping board! Lay the chicken between two sheets of #clingfilm{}. Whack the chicken with a #rolling pin{} or the base of a pan until it is 1cm thick.

Put a splash of @olive oil{1} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Season the chicken on both sides with @salt{} and some @black pepper{}. Once the oil is hot, fry the chicken for ~{4%minutes} on each side then remove from the pan.

> TIP: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once your potatoes are cooked, remove them from the pan with a #slotted spoon{} and put them in a large #bowl{}. Keep the pan of water boiling and use it to cook the green beans until tender with a little bit of bite left, ~{3-4%minutes}. When they are cooked, drain the beans in a #colander{} and put them in a bowl of cold water to stop them going soft.

In a #small bowl{}, mix the @Cider & Horseradish Wholegrain Mustard{1} with the @red wine vinegar{1/2} and @olive oil{1}(amount specified). Season with @salt{} and @black pepper{} and stir in the spring onion.

> TIP: If you happen to have a lemon in the fruit bowl then a little grating of zest would be good here too.

Pour the dressing over the potatoes and add the celery and parsley. Drain the green beans again and add them too. Lastly stir through the @sour cream{1/2} and toss gently to combine evenly. Serve on plates then slice the chicken and lay it over the top. Enjoy!